        "text_673jrG": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When a brief and painless electrical impulse is applied to the fingertip, it stimulates a measurable electro-photonic emission. This light emission results from interactions between the electromagnetic field and the skin’s surface, influenced by microcirculation, skin conductivity, and autonomic nervous system activity.</p><p>The emitted photons are captured by a specialized optical system and recorded as digital images. These images reflect physiological regulation patterns rather than anatomical structures.</p>",
